nter their password or ‘sign in’ again upon return visits to the website. Cookies allow our servers to keep track of customer details between visits to our website.\r\n\r\nThe information stored by the cookie includes the data that is provided during online registration. This information is only accessible online when a customer enters their username and password. Other information stored by a cookie includes website traffic data. This is not used to identify individual details but only collated into aggregate anonymous results in order to evaluate and improve our shopping service for our customers.\r\n\r\nCredit Card Information is never stored in the cookie.\r\n\r\nYou do not have to accept cookies in order to use our website and you may adjust your web browser in order to be notified when you receive a cookie or to reject cookies, however if you choose to reject cookies there may be some loss of functionality of our website and convenience of product and other offerings to you.\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n	<li><strong> Email Addresses</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe will store your email address if you send us a query, place an order or subscribe to an email list. Your email address is used for the purpose you provide it for and statistical information only, and is never disclosed to any third parties for any other purpose without your consent.\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n	<li><strong> Spam</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe will never knowingly send you electronic messages without your consent, however we may send you information about the products and services that we offer, opportunities that may be of benefit to you and the like. You may inform us at any time if you do not wish to receive any such information from us.\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n	<li><strong> Data Security</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe will take all reasonable steps to preserve the privacy of your personal information. Our order processing system is protected by a firewall, when you make an online purchase from us. A firewall is a hardware and software security system designed to filter specified exchanges of information and restrict access to authorised systems and users. When you place an order online our website encrypts and passes all of the order information supplied to our back-office system, which is not connected directly to the internet.\r\n\r\nCrucially, unencrypted credit card details will not be stored on our server, and will be sent only in encrypted form. The encryption technology we use is the industry standard SSL (Secure Socket Layers).\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n	<li><strong> Where are our servers located?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe Personal Information which you provide to us may be stored on our contractor’s servers that may be from time to time located outside of Australia.\r\n\r\nWe are able to extract any data stored on overseas servers on to our servers as a back up on a regular basis.\r\n<ol start=\"11\">\r\n	<li><strong> Transfer of Your Personal Information</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe will only transfer your personal information to a business advisor, contractor or related entity whether in Australia or in a foreign country if the transfer is to a recipient that has covenanted to be bound by this Policy and that is subject to a law or contract which upholds the principles for the fair handling of personal information in a manner similar to the National Privacy Principles or you consent to the transfer or the transfer is necessary for the performance of providing contracted products or services to you or we have taken reasonable steps to ensure that the personal information which is to be transferred will not be held, used or disclosed by the recipient of the information in any way which is inconsistent with the National Privacy Principles.\r\n<ol start=\"12\">\r\n	<li><strong> Changes to this Privacy Policy</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nKate Morgan Weight loss may be required to change the terms of this Privacy Policy from time to time due to changing business requirements or changes in the law. Kate Morgan Weigh loss reserves the right to change the Privacy Policy at any time and any changes effected to the Privacy Policy by us will be included in the updated Privacy Policy appearing on this website under the privacy policy link.\r\n\r\nContinued use of the website by you is deemed acceptance of the amended terms of the Privacy Policy.\r\n<ol start=\"13\">\r\n	<li><strong> Feedback and Complaints Handling Procedure</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe welcome your feedback and will attend to all complaints received by you promptly and in a proper manner. Please email, fax or write to our Privacy Officer using the contact information below.\r\n\r\nIf you are unable to resolve your concern or query with our Privacy Officer, you may contact the Federal Privacy Commissioner regarding lodging of a complaint. The Commissioner’s website is www.privacy.gov.au or the telephone number is 1300 363 992.\r\n<ol start=\"14\">\r\n	<li><strong> Who to Contact if you have any Privacy Concerns or Queries</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf you have any questions about our Privacy Policy or the manner in which we deal with your personal information, please contact us','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','221-revision-v1','','','2015-06-30 15:28:39','2015-06-30 05:28:39','',221,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/221-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(223,1,'2015-06-30 15:37:30','2015-06-30 05:37:30','','ISH_24890_KM_Homepage_DD2b','','inherit','open','open','','ish_24890_km_homepage_dd2b','','','2015-06-30 15:37:30','2015-06-30 05:37:30','',74,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/05/ISH_24890_KM_Homepage_DD2b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(224,1,'2015-06-30 15:37:39','2015-06-30 05:37:39','','Home','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-v1','','','2015-06-30 15:37:39','2015-06-30 05:37:39','',74,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/74-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(225,1,'2015-06-30 15:38:02','2015-06