Fish (e.g. Barramundi, Perch, Snapper, Gurnard and Hoki)</li>\r\n	<li>Calamari (not crumbed)</li>\r\n	<li>Prawns or Shellfish (no more than 1 serve per week)</li>\r\n	<li>1⁄2 cup Low Fat Cottage Cheese 1⁄2 cup Low Fat Ricotta Cheese</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Salmon and Tuna in oil</li>\r\n	<li>Deep Fried or Fried Fish</li>\r\n	<li>Cheese</li>\r\n	<li>Milk</li>\r\n	<li>Long Life Milk</li>\r\n	<li>Flavoured Milk</li>\r\n	<li>Milk Powder</li>\r\n	<li>Cream</li>\r\n	<li>Coconut Cream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-523\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/food-guide.jpg\" alt=\"food guide\" width=\"1822\" height=\"1260\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;<h3>Seafood/dairy products (protein source)</h3><table border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"10px\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><h3>Allowed</h3><p>(Serving size is a palm size - average 120 grams women and 200 grams men)</p></td><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><h3>Not allowed</h3></td></tr><tr><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><ul><li>Tinned Salmon (in water only)</li><li>Asparagus</li><li>Beans</li><li>Bok Choy</li><li>Broccoli</li><li>Brussels Sprouts</li><li>Cabbage</li><li>Celery</li><li>Cucumber</li><li>Capsicum</li><li>Carrots (max. ½ cup per day)</li><li>Cauliflower</li><li>Lettuce</li><li>Leeks</li><li>Mushrooms</li><li>Parsley</li><li>Radish</li><li>Shallots</li><li>Snow Peas</li><li>Spinach</li><li>Squash (Scallopini)</li><li>Tomato (max. 2 per day)</li><li>Sprouts (bean, alfalfa, etc)</li><li>Eggplant</li><li>Onions</li><li>Zucchini</li></ul></td><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><ul><li>Avocado</li><li>Beetroot</li><li>Corn</li><li>Parsnip</li><li>Peas</li><li>Potatoes</li><li>Pumpkin</li><li>Sweet Potato</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-531\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/food-guide2.jpg\" alt=\"food guide2\" width=\"2279\" height=\"1557\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Prepared meals (protein source)</h3><table border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"10px\"><tbody><tr><td><h3>Allowed</h3><p>(Serving size is a palm size - average 120 grams women and 200 grams men)</p></td><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><h3>Not allowed</h3></td></tr><tr><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><p><strong>SHELF GOODS - KRAFT</strong></p><ul><li>Braised Steak and Onions (can)</li></ul><p><strong>FROZEN FISH - SEALORDS</strong></p><ul><li>Dory Fillet Lite</li><li>Hoki Fillets Lite (NZ Only)</li><li>Simply Natural Dory and Hoki (AUS Only)</li></ul><p><strong>FROZEN FISH FILLETS</strong></p><p><strong>Grill Bakes</strong></p><ul><li>Lemon Glaze&nbsp;</li><li>Light and Tangy Glaze</li><li>Mediterranean Glaze</li><li>Mild Sweet Chilli Glaze</li><li>Hoki Fillets</li></ul><p><strong>FROZEN CHICKEN - INGHAM</strong></p><p><strong>Chicken Breast Steaks</strong></p><ul><li>Lemon and Coriander</li><li>Original</li><li>Lite Chicken Breast Fillets</li><li>Garlic Lemon and Herbs</li><li>Lime and Coriander (NZ Only)</li></ul><p><strong>TEGAL (NZ ONLY)</strong></p><ul><li>Char-grill Style Chicken Breast</li><li>Steaks</li></ul><p><strong>FRONZEN STEAK</strong></p><p><strong>FROZEN SOUPS</strong></p><p><b>Lean Cuisine</b></p><ul><li>Grilled Tomato and Basil Soup</li></ul></td><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><ul><li>Pies</li><li>Pastries</li><li>Pizza</li><li>Chips</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><h3>&nbsp;</h3><h3>Fruit (2 pieces per day)</h3><table border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"10px\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><h3>Allowed</h3><p>(Serving size is a palm size - average 120 grams women and 200 grams men)</p></td><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><h3>Not allowed</h3></td></tr><tr><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><ul><li>Apple (both red and green)</li><li>Apricots</li><li>Banana (max. 1 per day)</li><li>Blackberries</li><li>Cherries</li><li