v1','','','2015-08-06 14:50:19','2015-08-06 04:50:19','',422,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/422-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(484,1,'2015-07-13 15:03:29','2015-07-13 05:03:29','<a href=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Fennel-Orange-Salad.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-386\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Fennel-Orange-Salad.jpg\" alt=\"Fennel-Orange-Salad\" width=\"110\" height=\"73\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 small fennel bulb</li>\r\n	<li>1 peeled orange</li>\r\n	<li>½ red onion</li>\r\n	<li>1 tablespoon white wine vinegar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nFinely slice the fennel and onion. Cut orange into chunks. Toss together and sprinkle with vinegar.','Fennel & Orange','','inherit','open','open','','422-revision-v1','','','2015-07-13 15:03:29','2015-07-13 05:03:29','',422,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/422-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(485,1,'2015-07-13 15:04:08','2015-07-13 05:04:08','<a href=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Simple-Vegetable-Stir-Fry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-427\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Simple-Vegetable-Stir-Fry.jpg\" alt=\"Simple-Vegetable-Stir-Fry\" width=\"131\" height=\"101\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 celery Stalk, finely sliced</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup of bean sprouts</li>\r\n	<li>1 onion, finely sliced</li>\r\n	<li>1 carrot, cut into Julienne</li>\r\n	<li>1 red capsicum, cut into Julienne</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup of snow peas</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup sugar snap peas</li>\r\n	<li>4 mushrooms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMarinade:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons splenda</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 teaspoon fresh ginger</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 teaspoon fresh garlic</li>\r\n	<li>1/4 cup Tamari (Japanese soy sauce)</li>\r\n	<li>1 stalk lemongrass</li>\r\n	<li>1/4 cup water</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nGently fry onion in a wok with 2 tablespoons of water until soft. Add the carrots, celery and capsicum and sautee until tender. Add remaining vegetables and toss to combine. Place marinade ingredients into a food processor and blend until combined. Pour marinade over vegetables and stir to combined.','Stir Fried Vegetables','','inherit','open','open','','425-revision-v1','','','2015-07-13 15:04:08','2015-07-13 05:04:08','',425,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/425-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(486,1,'2015-07-13 16:04:29','2015-07-13 06:04:29','<a href=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/default.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/default.jpg\" alt=\"default\" width=\"211\" height=\"140\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>½ onion, cut into chucks</li>\n	<li>1 carrot, in 2cm slices</li>\n	<li>1 stalk celery, in 2cm pieces</li>\n	<li>1 up cauliflower, in pieces</li>\n	<li>½ cup broccoli, in pieces</li>\n	<li>½ cup green beans, in 5cm pieces</li>\n	<li>2 teaspoons mild curry paste</li>\n	<li>1 cup vegetable stock</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Method</strong>\n\nHeat a non-stick pan, add onion and cook for 1 minute. Stir in curry paste, add carrots, celery, cauliflower and stock. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and beans and cook for 3 minutes. Serve.','Curried Vegetables','','inherit','open','open','','430-autosave-v1','','','2015-07-13 16:04:29','2015-07-13 06:04:29','',430,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/430-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(487,1,'2015-07-13 16:04:32','2015-07-13 06:04:32','<a href=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/default.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/default.jpg\" alt=\"default\" width=\"211\" height=\"140\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>½ onion, cut into chucks</li>\r\n	<li>1 carrot, in 2cm slices</li>\r\n	<li>1 stalk celery, in 2cm pieces</li>\r\n	<li>1 up cauliflower, in pieces</li>\r\n	<li>½ cup broccoli, in pieces</li>\r\n	<li>½ cup green beans, in 5cm pieces</li>\r\n	<li>2 teaspoons mild curry paste</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup vegetable stock</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nHeat a non-stick pan, add onion and cook for 1 minute. Stir in curry paste, add carrots, celery, cauliflower and stock. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and beans and cook for 3 minutes. Serve.','Curried Vegetables','','inherit','open','open','','430-revision-v1','','','2015-07-13 16:04:32','2015-07-13 06:04:32','',430,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/430-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(488,1,'2015-07-13 16:05:02','2015-07-13 06:05:02','&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>2 sticks rosemary, to brush BBQ</li>\n	<li>1 red capsicum, cut into batons</li>\n	<li>1 yellow capsicum, cut into batons</li>\n	<li>1 medium zucchini, cut into batons</li>\n	<li>1 bunch asparagus, trimmed and cut in half sea salt and freshly ground black pepper</li>\n	<li>1 tablespoon seeded mustard</li>\n	<li>½ lemon cut into segments</li>\n	<li>½ red onion, sliced thinly</li>\n	<li>2 ripe juicy roma tomatoes, roughly chopped</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Method</strong>\n\nPreheat BBQ to a medium-high heat. Brush BBQ with rosemary. Cook vegetables on BBQ until tender. Remove and place on a serving plate. In a large mixing bowl, combine mustard, salt and pepper, lemon segments, onion, tomato and basil. Stir to combine. Spoon over and serve.','BBQ Mediterranean vegetables with fresh tomato, lemon & basil dressing','','inherit','open','open','','428-autosave-v1','','','2015-07-13 16:05:02','2015-07-13 06:05:02','',428,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/428-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(489,1,'2015-07-13 16:05:16','2015-07-13 06:05:16','<a href=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/default.jpg\"><