8/Chicken-Salad-with-Snow-Pea-Broccoli_30-A-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Chicken Salad with Snow Pea &amp; Broccoli_30 A\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>120g chicken tenderloin (approx 4)</li>\r\n	<li>100g snow peas, blanched</li>\r\n	<li>125g broccoli flowers, blanched</li>\r\n	<li>½ green pepper, sliced</li>\r\n	<li>2 spring onions, sliced</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Dressing</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>¼ cup lemon juice</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon Dijon mustard</li>\r\n	<li>1 tablespoon chopped parsley</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon grated ginger</li>\r\n	<li>¼ cup water</li>\r\n	<li>½ teaspoon sesame oil</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nPoach, steam or microwave chicken. Drain and cool.\r\n\r\nMix chicken with vegetables in a bowl. Whisk together ingredients for the dressing.\r\n\r\nPour over, toss, and serve.','Chicken, Snow Peas & Broccoli','','publish','closed','closed','','chicken-with-snow-peas-broccoli','','','2015-08-12 14:36:27','2015-08-12 04:36:27','',390,'http://174.121.78.227/?page_id=740',0,'page','',0),(741,1,'2015-08-06 13:20:56','2015-08-06 03:20:56','','Chicken Salad with Snow Pea & Broccoli_30 A','','inherit','open','open','','chicken-salad-with-snow-pea-broccoli_30-a','','','2015-08-06 13:20:56','2015-08-06 03:20:56','',740,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/08/Chicken-Salad-with-Snow-Pea-Broccoli_30-A.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(742,1,'2015-08-06 13:21:24','2015-08-06 03:21:24','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-741\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/08/Chicken-Salad-with-Snow-Pea-Broccoli_30-A-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Chicken Salad with Snow Pea &amp; Broccoli_30 A\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>120g chicken tenderloin (approx 4)</li>\r\n	<li>100g snow peas, blanched</li>\r\n	<li>125g broccoli flowers, blanched</li>\r\n	<li>½ green pepper, sliced</li>\r\n	<li>2 spring onions, sliced</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDressing:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>¼ cup lemon juice/li&gt;</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon Dijon mustard</li>\r\n	<li>1 tablespoon chopped parsley</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon grated ginger</li>\r\n	<li>¼ cup water</li>\r\n	<li>½ teaspoon sesame oil</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nPoach, steam or microwave chicken. Drain and cool.\r\n\r\nMix chicken with vegetables in a bowl. Whisk together ingredients for the dressing.\r\n\r\nPour over, toss, and serve.','Chicken Salad with Snow Peas & Broccoli','','inherit','open','open','','740-revision-v1','','','2015-08-06 13:21:24','2015-08-06 03:21:24','',740,'http://174.121.78.227/740-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(744,1,'2015-08-06 13:26:29','2015-08-06 03:26:29','<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-743 size-medium\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Chicken-with-Mango-Salsa_38-A-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Chicken with Mango Salsa_38 A\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>120g chicken breast, skin off</li>\r\n	<li>½ mango, peeled and cut into cubes</li>\r\n	<li>¼ red onion, diced</li>\r\n	<li>¼ lebanese cucumber, diced</li>\r\n	<li>¼ red chilli (seeds removed), diced</li>\r\n	<li>½ teaspoon finely grated ginger</li>\r\n	<li>1 tablespoon chopped coriander (or mint) juice of half a lime</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nGrill chicken on BBQ or pan until cooked. Combine all other ingredients to make salsa. Serve with chicken','Chicken with Mango Salsa','','inherit','open','open','','433-revision-v1','','','2015-08-06 13:26:29','2015-08-06 03:26:29','',433,'http://174.121.78.227/433-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(745,1,'2015-08-06 13:51:58','2015-08-06 03:51:58','','Chilli Chicken_41 A','','inherit','open','open','','chilli-chicken_41-a','','','2015-08-06 13:51:58','2015-08-06 03:51:58','',436,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/Chilli-Chicken_41-A.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(746,1,'2015-08-06 13:52:41','2015-08-06 03:52:41','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>120g chicken breast, skin off</li>\r\n	<li>1 tablespoon oyster sauce</li>\r\n	<li>¼ teaspoon chilli powder</li>\r\n	<li>½ clove garlic crushed</li>\r\n	<li>Mix together and coat chicken. Bake chicken in oven at 175 on non stick baking paper for 20 minutes, turning once.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMake tomato sauce by combining:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>½ cup tomato puree</li>\r\n	<li>3 tablespoons water</li>\r\n	<li>1 celery stick, finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>½ onion, finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>½ green pepper, finely chopped</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nIn a small saucepan. Bring to boil then simmer uncovered for about 5 minutes, until slightly thickened. Serve over chicken.','Chilli Chicken','','inherit','open','open','','436-revision-v1','','','2015-08-06 13:52:41','2015-08-06 03:52:41','',436,'http://174.121.78.227/436-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(747,1,'2015-08-06 13:52:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2015-08-06 13:52:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://174.121.78.227/?page_id=747',0,'page','',0),(748,1,'2015-08-06 13:55:31','2015-08-06 03:55:31','[child_pages cols=\"3\" id=\"390\" thumbs=\"true\" hide_more=\"true\" link_titles=\"true\" hide_excerpt=\"true\" link_thumbs=\"true\" skin=\"simple\" class=\"recipes\"]','Chicken','','inherit','open','open','','390-revision-v1','','','2015-08-06 13:55:31','2015-08-06 03:55:31','',390,'http://174.121.78.227/390-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(750,1,'2015-08-06 14:03:26','2015-08-06 04:03:26','','BBQ Squid & Octopus Salad_09 01 A','','inherit','open','open','','bbq-squid-octopus-salad_09-01-a','','','2015-08-06 14:03:26','2015-08-06 04:03:26','',465,'http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/BBQ-Squid-Octopus-Salad_09-01-A.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(751,1,'2015-08-06 14:04:05','2015-08-06 04:04:05','<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-750 size-medium\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/07/BBQ-Squid-Octopus-Salad_09-01-A-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"BBQ Squid &amp; Octopus Salad_09 01 A\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>120g baby octopus or squid</li>\r\n	<li>½ green chilli, finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>1 clove garlic, crushed</li>\r\n	<li>2 asparagus spears, cooked and chopped</li>\r\n	<li>6 yellow or cherry tomatoes</li>\r\n	<li>1 gherkin, finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>½ an orange, peeled and sliced 100g rocket</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\r\nMix chilli and garlic with squid and octopus. Leave to marinate in fridge for up to 3 hours. Cook on BBQ or grill plate, turning, for 3 minutes until just cooked. Make a salad with remaining ingredients, place cooked seafood on top.\r\n\r\nThen make a dressing with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>¼ cup orange juice</li>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons vinegar</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon grated orange rind</li>\r\n	<li>1 cm ginger, peeled and grated</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMix together, pour over salad and serve.','BBQ Squid & Octopus Salad','','inherit','open','open','','465-revision-v1','','','2015-08-06 14:04:05','2015-08-06 04:04:05','',465,'http://174.121.78.227/465-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(752,1,'2015-08-06 14:07:19','2015-08-06 04:07:19','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-753\" src=\"http://174.121.78.227/~kmxmarketing/resources/uploads/2015/08/Lemon-Pepper-Tuna-Salad_24-A-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Lemon Pepper Tuna Salad_24 A\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 small can tuna, in brine</li>\r\n	<li>100g green beans, steamed and sliced</li>\r\n	<li>3 radishes, trimmed and quartered</li>\r\n	<li>½ red onion, thinly sliced</li>\r\n	<li>1 tomato, cored and quartered</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon lemon pepper seasoning</li>\r\n	<li>2 teaspoons lemon juice</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon lemon rind, grated</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Method</strong>\r\n\